Secondary Science - Dubai- August 2014
03 May 2014 08:24 PM - UAE
A Secondary Science Teacher with at least 2 years of post-qualification teaching experience who can also deliver some Grade 6/7 ICT classes is needed for this very well run, highly respected school in Dubai.  Broadly international, with a strong investment in teacher development and welfare, this is an excellent school in which to start or continue your international teaching career.  The school  teaches the National Curriculum to GCSE/IGCSE at secondary, followed by the IB diploma but for this post teaching will not go over IGCSE and the Science can be any specialism. Teachers who have relevant experience are preferred to those who do not, particularly early in the hiring season. The staff and students come from over 50 nationalities and the school genuinely embraces and values their mutliculturalism. The school provides mostly shared housing in the first year (large flat/own bedroom of course), with a generous housing allowance in subequent years that will enable a teacher to find their own housing afterwards.  Flights are yearly.  This is a highly recommended school that takes excellent care of its teaching staff and has done so for years. The salaries are
